nine americans terry anderson chief middle east correspondent for 
the associated press has been held captive longest he was 
kidnapped on march 16 1985 
jacobsen 57 was released by his captors in beirut on nov 2 
1986 after being held for 17 months he was working as the 
hospital administrator at the american university hospital in 
beirut when he was seized on may 28 1985 
jacobsen said the petition specifically asks fadlallah to join 
us in prayer for the safe return home of anglican church envoy 
terry waite who was taken hostage last year while trying to 
negotiate the release of other western captives 
the petition concludes we share with you the desire to see 
all people safe and at peace and we agree with your statement 
neither islam nor christianity justify kidnapping 
the petition was organized by friends in the west a small 
protestant group based in seattle wash that has worked quietly 
but tirelessly for the release of the hostages since 1986 jacobsen 
said 
jacobsen asked that the leader of friends in the west not be 
named saying it may endanger his life or his freedom in further 
efforts to free the hostages 
