the berge strand headed to the southern gulf port of dubai 
where the ace chemi is docked for repairs 
the us central command meanwhile said the navys 32nd convoy 
of the year was sailing south through the gulf it included one 
usflagged kuwaiti tanker the 46723ton gas prince escorted by 
the missile frigate copeland 
a fire on the 6730ton ace chemi forced its japanese captain 
and 16 south korean crewmen to abandon ship all were reported 
rescued by salvage tugs 
the raid on the chemical tanker was the first by iran since the 
united states implemented a new policy may 3 that permits us navy 
ships to intervene in attacks on commercial vessels on request 
regardless of the flag they are flying 
us ships were unable to respond to the ace chemi raid because 
the closest us navy vessel was 60 miles away a twohour sail 
said us navy sources 
the attacks on the japanese and norwegian ships occurred about 
11 miles south of irans offshore larak oil terminal where iraqi 
warplanes on saturday devastated the worlds largest tanker the 
564739ton seawise giant and four other ships 
the unofficial death toll stood at 34 after iraqi f1 mirage 
jets streaked into larak following a 750mile run down the gulf 
the seawise giant chartered by iran as a storage ship had been 
unloading oil to the spanish ship barcelona at larak tankers pick 
up oil brought down the gulf by irans fleet of shuttle tankers 
baghdad has claimed a dozen raids six of which were 
independently verified on iranian tankers and terminals since 
april 29 the raids seek to strangle oil exports that support 
tehrans side of the 7yearold gulf war 
iranian officials recently declared that their policy of 
blowforblow retaliatory attacks on neutral shipping would 
continue but wednesdays was the first since april 24 
about 350 seamen have been killed and hundreds of others injured 
in attacks on more than 500 vessels in gulf waterways in the 
spillover of the iraniraq land war which began in september 1980 
in the ground war irans official islamic republic news agency 
said iranian forces killed or wounded 2000 iraqi troops and 
captured more than 10 square miles of northeast iraq in an 
operation that began tuesday night it said many iraqi troops were 
taken prisoner there was no comment from iraq 
