military delegation on a fiveday visit to china the official 
xinhua news agency reported the delegation returns to north korea 
friday 
the 83yearold senior leader went into semiretirement last 
fall and has made rare public appearances 
the nationally televised evening news showed deng looking fit 
and alert greeting o with a hug and kisses on both cheeks 
i often tell my colleagues to be brave and not be afraid of 
risks because otherwise no progress will be made deng told the 
north koreans 
he made the statement while talking about drastic price reforms 
that have raised the prices of four staple foods by as much as 60 
percent 
the price increases went into effect in beijing four days ago 
raising the prices of eggs pork vegetables and sugar by 28 
percent to 60 percent they created much grumbling among consumers 
already unhappy about skyrocketing prices 
chinas current price reform is a bold yet risky action but 
the countrys leadership is confident of doing a good job deng 
said 
he said the price increases are necessary because food prices in 
the past were kept artificially low through government subsidies 
deng said reform of the price of raw materials would follow the 
rise in food prices 
resolving the price problem is imperative to chinas economic 
progress and its attainment of the goal of reaching 
developedcountry status by the middle of the next century 
xinhua reported deng as saying 
chinas leadership knows every step the country takes involves 
risks and it could encounter difficulties deng said the party 
and the masses have to understand this is a demanding task 
