<TEXT>
chrysler has begun installing driversside air 
bags as standard equipment on three of its models and will add them 
this week to three more becoming the first us automaker to make 
air bags standard equipment 
federal safety regulations require increased use of passive 
restraints such as air bags which inflate in event of a 
collision or automatic seat belts twentyfive percent of 1988 
vehicles must have them 40 percent in 1989 and 100 percent by 1990 
chrysler said wednesday it began installing driversside air 
bags on dodge daytona chrysler lebaron coupe and lebaron 
convertible models after may 1 beginning saturday its large 
rearwheeldrive sedans chrysler fifth avenue dodge diplomat and 
plymouth gran fury will have them however chrysler plans to 
stop building those three cars at years end 
the no 3 automaker said it will tout the air bagequipped 
models in a twopage advertisement featuring chairman lee iacocca 
and a drawing showing how the device works the ad will run in 14 
magazines and newspapers next week 
the air bags inflate within onetwentieth of a second after 
electronic sensors detect the beginning of an impact that would be 
comparable to hitting a wall at 10 miles an hour or faster the 
bags stored in the center of the steering wheel deflate almost 
immediately 
chrysler offers motorized automatic lap and shoulder belts on 
the imported conquest and eagle medallion and plans to include them 
on the dodge shadow plymouth sundance and eagle premier later this 
year said spokesman tom houston 
ford motor co the nations secondlargest automaker offers 
air bags as optional equipment on its ford tempo and mercury topaz 
compact cars plans to add more models by 1990 and may include them 
as standard equipment on one highend 1989 model 
ford uses automatic motorized front seat belts on several models 
including the ford escort one of its topselling cars 
general motors corp the nations largest automaker offers the 
bags as options on the 1988 oldsmobile delta 88 plans to offer 
them on an additional car line in 1989 and plans to make them 
standard equipment on some 1990 models 
automatic front seat belts already are standard on many gm 
models 
</TEXT>
