authorized to aid neutral merchant vesels which seek help 
reagan has refused to invoke the law even though there have 
been four separate clashes between the navy and iran congress has 
debated trying to invoke the law but has been unable to agree on 
whether that should be done 
last year 115 legislators went to federal court and filed suit 
seeking an order directing reagan to invoke the law but the suit 
was thrown out of court and the legislators are now appealing that 
ruling 
mitchell said the law was well intentioned but it has not 
worked we have spent countless hours proposing filibustering and 
debating measures to invoke a law rather than assessing the 
wisdom of the policy that prompted the deployment of forces 
sen sam nunn dga chairman of the armed services committee 
said theres an old saying that if something isnt broke dont 
fix it well the war powers act is broken and it should be fixed 
nunn said the law encourages confrontation rather than 
consultation between the presidents and congress when forces are 
introduced the debate in the congress is frequently on procedure 
rather than policy 
warner said many of the problems in the current law arise 
because every president resents a diminuation in his power 
the law was approved in november 1973 despite the veto by nixon 
the house voted 284135 to override nixons veto while the senate 
vote was 7518 
backers of the law argued that it was needed because nixons 
vietnam policies were usurping the congressional right to declare 
war 
since the law was enacted presidents have formally submitted 
reports on a dozen occasions although they have rarely cited the 
section of the law which triggers the 60day time period for a 
congressional vote 
</TEXT>
