moodys investors service inc has assigned a 
singlea3 rating to 300 million west german marks of eurobonds 
issued by china and due in 1992 moodys japanese subsidiary said 
moodys japan kk said in a statement wednesday that it was the 
first time a bond issued by china had been rated by a us 
creditrating agency the singlea3 rating indicates that the 
eurobond issue is a safe investment 
moodys rates bonds in 27 categories from singlec3 the 
highest investment risk to triplea1 the lowest risk 
the moodys statement said the rating was based on chinas 
current low level of debt the expectation that future borrowing 
will remain within a comfortable range relative to the nations 
debtservicing capacity and the progress made in stabilizing 
chinese politics since the death of chairman mao zedong in 1976 
moodys said chinas foreign debt is low by international 
standards totaling an estimated 27 billion at the end of last 
year that represents 93 percent of chinas gross national product 
and 75 percent of its current foreignexchange receipts the 
statement said 
china has adopted a conservative policy toward reliance on 
foreign debt and this policy is likely to continue the 
statement said 
however it said the scope and the nature of the changes 
underway are unprecedented with major policy contradictions yet to 
be resolved 
discontent has emerged primarily because of the dramatic 
shifts in the control of resources and in the distribution of 
benefits but also because progress on political liberalization has 
been slow the statement said 
