<TEXT>
a federal appeals judge on thursday halted a 
shareholder vote scheduled for friday over control of allegheny 
international inc the second time in this week the vote has been 
blocked 
judge carol los mansmann of the 3rd circuit court of appeals in 
philadelphia postponed the vote scheduled to take place at 
alleghenys annual meeting until the federal court could review 
the case a review was expected next week 
on wednesday us district judge alan bloch had overturned a 
us bankruptcy courts order issued monday that blocked the 
meeting 
bloch said the proxy vote could be stopped only if there was 
fraud violence or other illegalities 
two new york investment firms are leading a proxy fight by 
dissident shareholders to gain control of the pittsburgh consumer 
products company the group has nominated candidates for seven of 
13 seats on the allegheny international board of directors 
unsecured creditors claim that a change in management would 
delay the companys emergence from bankruptcy proceedings and have 
asked the appeals court to cancel the proxy vote 
company management also opposes the dissidents claiming they 
have no experience in the companys business and no definite plan 
for the future 
</TEXT>
